1] find/search algo
  > works on o(n) time
  -> eg. find(arr, arr+n, key)
  -> returns an iterator to the found key
  > to get the exact index, subtract base address from the iterator.
    e.g. index = it-arr;

2] binary_search (sorted arrays) 
  > works in o(logn) time
  > e.g. binary_search(arr, arr+n, key)
  -> returns a bool if element is present
  > to get the exact index, only if binary search return true, 2 functions are present
    > lower_bound ==> returns the iterator of element >= key
    > upper_bound ==> returns the next greater element

3] sort 
  > time complexity o(nlogn)

